quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  6,111,"And if We had sent down to them the angels and the dead had spoken to them and (even if) We had gathered everything before them, face to face, still, they were not to believe unless Allah would have so willed. But, most of them go for ignorance."
  6,112,"And similarly, We have made enemies for every prophet, the satans of mankind and jinn. They reveal to one another ornamented words in order to deceive. And had Allah willed, they would have not done so. So, leave them with what they forge"
  6,113,"and in order that the hearts of those who do not believe in the Hereafter may incline to it and so that they commit what they are to commit."
  6,114,"So, is it someone apart from Allah that I should seek as judge while He has sent down to you the Book with de-tails? And those We have given the Book know that it is something revealed from your Lord with the truth. So, never be one of those who are suspicious."
  6,115,"And the Word of your Lord is perfect in truth and justice. None is there to change His words, and He is All-Hearing, All-Knowing."
  6,116,"And if you obey the majority of those on earth, they will make you lose the way of Allah. They follow nothing but whims, and they do nothing but make conjectures."
  6,117,"Surely, your Lord knows best those who go astray from His way, and He is the best knower of those who are on the right path."
  6,118,"So, eat of that upon which the name of Allah has been invoked, if you do believe in His verses."